# PHASE 1 — SonarQube Server Setup

## STEP 1 — Launch SonarQube EC2

```
AWS Console → EC2 → Launch Instance

Name          = sonarqube-server
AMI           = Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
Instance type = m7i-flex.large
Storage       = 20 GB

Security Group:
→ HTTP port 9000 → Anywhere okay!
```

---

## STEP 2 — SSH into SonarQube EC2

```bash
ssh -i your-key.pem ubuntu@<SONARQUBE-EC2-IP>
```

---

## STEP 3 — Install Java

```bash
sudo apt update -y
sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y

# Verify
java -version
```

---

## STEP 4 — Download and Install SonarQube

```bash
wget https://binaries.sonarsource.com/Distribution/sonarqube/sonarqube-10.3.0.82913.zip
sudo apt install unzip -y
unzip sonarqube-10.3.0.82913.zip
sudo mv sonarqube-10.3.0.82913 /opt/sonarqube
```

---

## STEP 5 — Create SonarQube User

```bash
# NOTE: SonarQube cannot run as root
# Must create separate user okay!
sudo adduser --system --no-create-home --group --disabled-login sonarqube
sudo chown -R sonarqube:sonarqube /opt/sonarqube
```

---

## STEP 6 — Start SonarQube

```bash
# Start as sonarqube user (NOT root)
sudo -u sonarqube /opt/sonarqube/bin/linux-x86-64/sonar.sh start

# Wait 2 minutes then check status
sudo -u sonarqube /opt/sonarqube/bin/linux-x86-64/sonar.sh status
# Should show: SonarQube is running okay!
```

---

## STEP 7 — Open SonarQube UI

```
Browser → http://<SONARQUBE-EC2-IP>:9000

Login:
Username = admin
Password = admin

First login → it will ask to change password
Set new password okay!
```

---

## STEP 8 — Generate SonarQube Token

```
SonarQube UI → Top right → Admin → My Account
→ Security tab
→ Generate Tokens

Name    = jenkins-token
Type    = User Token
Expires = No expiration
→ Click Generate
→ Copy token immediately
  (Cannot see it again!) okay!
```

